To demonstrate the effectiveness of our proposed method, we compare it with three categories of methods, including:
SingleSet, a single model that each client is trained with their local data without FL;
Centralized, a single model that is trained with the combination of all the local data, which serves as the upper-bound of FL models; and
eight state-of-the-art FL algorithms, including: (1) FedAvg
, a classical FL algorithm that is trained by averaging parameters of all the participating clients; (2) FedBN
, a FL algorithm that alleviates the client-shift by using batch normalization on each local client; (3) FedProx
, a FL algorithm that applies a proximal term to the local objective function; (4) SCAFFOLD
, a FL algorithm that uses control variates to correct the client-drift; (5) MOON
, a FL algorithm that utilizes the similarity between model representations to correct the local update; (6) FedReg
, a FL algorithm that regularizes locally trained parameters with the loss on generated pseudo data to alleviate knowledge forgetting; (7) FL-MRCM
, a federated MRI algorithm that aligns the latent features between the source and target clients; and (8) FedMRI

, a federated MRI algorithm that preserves the client-specific properties to improve the FL performance. For a fair comparison, we adopt Swin Transformers and a standard ConvNet head as the reconstruction network for each client among all the baselines.
